WEBVTT

00:00.751 --> 00:02.753
[♪♪♪]

00:02.753 --> 00:04.922
ELIZABETH:
While my world is on hold

00:04.922 --> 00:07.925
until Jack returns
from the Northern Territories,

00:07.925 --> 00:10.719
life goes on
in Hope Valley.

00:12.053 --> 00:14.932
The residents here
continue to work hard

00:14.932 --> 00:19.394
to keep our community thriving
and our families strong.

00:19.394 --> 00:23.064
Moving forward,
we must never forget the past.

00:23.064 --> 00:25.901
As always,
life presents challenges,

00:25.901 --> 00:29.196
but we rely on each other
to see them through.

00:29.196 --> 00:32.533
Clara, thank you for watching
the café while I'm gone.

00:32.533 --> 00:35.202
Sure. Dottie understands.
I'm not sure I do.

00:35.202 --> 00:37.579
You were called as a witness
for Gowen's defense?

00:37.579 --> 00:39.665
Yes.
But he's corrupt!

00:39.665 --> 00:42.417
He stole from the town
and then tried to cover it up.

00:42.417 --> 00:44.252
Yes, he did do
all those things,

00:44.252 --> 00:45.671
but he has
done some good.

00:45.671 --> 00:47.631
I'm being called
as a character witness

00:47.631 --> 00:48.924
to talk about that.

00:48.924 --> 00:50.926
I hope he knows
he's lucky to have you.

00:50.926 --> 00:52.093
Henry's
a complicated man.

00:52.093 --> 00:53.637
My father told me
to stay away

00:53.637 --> 00:55.764
from complicated men.
Ha, good advice.

00:55.764 --> 00:57.558
How long will you
be gone, Abigail?

00:57.558 --> 01:00.101
Oh, not that long.
We're the last of the witnesses.

01:00.101 --> 01:01.020
"We"?

01:01.020 --> 01:04.231
[♪♪♪]

01:08.736 --> 01:10.445
LEE:
Make sure you tell 'em

01:10.445 --> 01:13.574
we need that replacement blade
by Tuesday, at the latest.

01:13.574 --> 01:14.491
Yes, sir.

01:14.491 --> 01:16.368
[GROANS]
You okay?

01:16.368 --> 01:18.245
Yeah,
it's just a stomachache.

01:18.245 --> 01:21.040
Well, make sure
Carson has a look at that, then.

01:21.999 --> 01:23.042
Bill.

01:23.042 --> 01:25.460
Bill! Hey!

01:25.460 --> 01:27.796
Well, you seem
awfully chipper.

01:27.796 --> 01:30.465
You don't.
I have to leave
town to testify.

01:30.465 --> 01:31.717
I hate going to court.

01:31.717 --> 01:33.552
A bunch of pretense,
if you ask me.

01:33.552 --> 01:35.554
Anyway, I have
a favor to ask.

01:35.554 --> 01:36.931
Sure. Fire away.

01:36.931 --> 01:39.349
I need to leave
someone in charge.

01:39.349 --> 01:40.726
Okay. In charge of what?

01:40.726 --> 01:42.269
Of the town.
As acting sheriff.

01:42.269 --> 01:43.645
[LAUGHS]
Me?

01:44.813 --> 01:46.607
Oh, you're serious?

01:46.607 --> 01:48.149
Oh... No, Bill.

01:48.149 --> 01:49.484
That's really not my thing.

01:49.484 --> 01:51.361
It's no one's thing,
till it is.

01:51.361 --> 01:52.654
[SIGHS]
Well...

01:52.654 --> 01:54.322
Right. Um...

01:54.322 --> 01:56.241
I would love to help you,
but...

01:56.241 --> 01:58.077
I just, I mean,
I have to run the mill.

01:58.077 --> 01:59.661
It'll only be
for a few days.

01:59.661 --> 02:01.038
You can send a wire
to Cape Fullerton

02:01.038 --> 02:02.873
if anything comes up
you can't handle.

02:02.873 --> 02:05.125
Oh! Good morning,
Bill.

02:05.125 --> 02:07.544
Hello, love of my life!
Mwah! Mm!

02:07.544 --> 02:10.047
LEE:
Thank you. Okay.

02:10.047 --> 02:12.132
What can I say?
We're a chipper family.

02:12.132 --> 02:14.468
What's going on?
I'm asking your husband

02:14.468 --> 02:16.095
to perform
his civic duties.

02:16.095 --> 02:17.012
He always does!

02:17.012 --> 02:18.722
Rosemary--
You do!

02:18.722 --> 02:21.308
You're the most civic-minded man
in all of Hope Valley!

02:21.308 --> 02:23.060
Sweetheart--
I knew I could
count on you.

02:23.060 --> 02:24.352
Raise your right hand.

02:24.352 --> 02:27.022
You're hereby
deputized.

02:27.022 --> 02:29.650
Oh! Did you just
become sheriff?

02:29.650 --> 02:31.485
Yes! Thanks to you.

02:31.485 --> 02:33.194
[LAUGHS]
Oh, you're welcome.

02:33.821 --> 02:36.031
[♪♪♪]

02:53.882 --> 02:56.217
So, let me
get this straight.

02:56.217 --> 02:58.929
Bill, you're testifying
for the prosecution,

02:58.929 --> 03:01.015
and you're testifying
for the defense?

03:01.015 --> 03:02.349
Yes, that's right.

03:02.349 --> 03:03.558
I'll be
giving facts.

03:03.558 --> 03:05.144
She'll be offering
her opinion.

03:05.144 --> 03:07.479
I'll be giving facts,
thank you very much.

03:07.479 --> 03:10.398
Oh! Well, should be
an interesting stagecoach ride.

03:10.398 --> 03:12.818
[LAUGHS]
Yes!

03:12.818 --> 03:15.278
Thank you
for watching Cody.

03:15.278 --> 03:16.488
Oh, it's my pleasure.

03:16.488 --> 03:17.698
After all,
we are family.

03:17.698 --> 03:20.826
Did I hear someone
say "family"?

03:20.826 --> 03:22.243
Julie?

03:22.243 --> 03:23.871
Oh! Oh, my goodness!

03:23.871 --> 03:25.413
Hi!
Hi!

03:25.413 --> 03:26.999
It's so good
to see you!

03:26.999 --> 03:28.167
[LAUGHING]

03:28.167 --> 03:29.376
Hi, Julie!
Welcome.

03:29.376 --> 03:30.794
It's nice
to have you back.

03:30.794 --> 03:31.837
Thank you.

03:31.837 --> 03:33.463
Oh! This is
my sister, Julie.

03:33.463 --> 03:35.841
Hi. Leland Coulter.
This is my wife, Rosemary.

03:35.841 --> 03:37.176
Pleasure.
Pleasure!

03:37.176 --> 03:39.178
You didn't write
to say you were coming.

03:39.178 --> 03:40.637
Well, I wanted
to surprise you.

03:40.637 --> 03:42.890
And you have certainly
accomplished that.

03:42.890 --> 03:44.224
I'll be back
in a few days

03:44.224 --> 03:45.726
and we can
to catch up then.

03:47.102 --> 03:49.688
Make sure there's a town here
when I get back.

03:49.688 --> 03:51.106
I will do my best.

03:51.106 --> 03:53.192
[BOTH GIGGLING]

03:53.192 --> 03:56.070
[♪♪♪]

04:02.034 --> 04:04.995
Got the coffee here.

04:06.413 --> 04:07.455
There you go.

04:07.455 --> 04:08.456
Can I top you up?

04:08.456 --> 04:09.583
Perfect.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.044
Enjoy.

04:15.214 --> 04:16.464
Coffee?

04:16.464 --> 04:18.299
Please.
Ha.

04:18.299 --> 04:20.969
You know what
I love about you?

04:20.969 --> 04:23.222
How dedicated you are
to everything you do.

04:23.222 --> 04:24.806
Even pouring coffee.

04:25.766 --> 04:27.226
But even you
need a break.

04:27.226 --> 04:29.228
Sit down,
have some breakfast with me.

04:29.228 --> 04:31.146
Jesse, I can't,
I have tables waiting.

04:31.146 --> 04:32.689
All right. You know,

04:32.689 --> 04:35.067
I'm really looking forward
to our date tonight.

04:35.067 --> 04:37.069
Me too.

04:37.069 --> 04:38.486
What's wrong?

04:39.571 --> 04:40.822
Nothing.

04:40.822 --> 04:42.157
Really?

04:43.242 --> 04:44.534
I've got to get back to it.

04:44.534 --> 04:47.454
Okay. I'll pick you up
around 6?

04:47.454 --> 04:48.413
Perfect.

04:48.413 --> 04:51.625
[♪♪♪]

04:57.547 --> 04:59.841
BILL:
Have you ever testified?

05:01.551 --> 05:03.470
I've never been
on a witness stand.

05:03.470 --> 05:04.679
Well, get ready.

05:04.679 --> 05:06.431
Bear traps
in every direction

05:06.431 --> 05:08.100
and vultures ready to pounce.

05:08.100 --> 05:09.977
You make it sound
pretty gruesome.

05:09.977 --> 05:12.104
Well, it can be.

05:13.772 --> 05:15.649
Do you think
Henry will go to prison?

05:15.649 --> 05:18.110
His crimes will dictate
his punishment, not me.

05:18.110 --> 05:19.987
Well, what we say
on the stand matters,

05:19.987 --> 05:21.488
or why else
would we be going?

05:21.488 --> 05:23.031
I'm going to present
the facts.

05:23.031 --> 05:26.534
Well, the fact is,
there is some good in Henry.

05:26.534 --> 05:28.954
Abigail, you tend to see
the good in people.

05:28.954 --> 05:30.705
My job is to see the bad,

05:30.705 --> 05:33.292
and there's a lot of bad
in Henry.

05:34.501 --> 05:36.711
[♪♪♪]

05:44.427 --> 05:47.806
Hmm. No fever.
Well, that's good.

05:47.806 --> 05:50.267
How long have you had
this abdominal pain, Mike?

05:50.267 --> 05:51.726
A few days.

05:51.726 --> 05:52.686
Any other symptoms?

05:52.686 --> 05:53.895
Any headaches
or sneezing?

05:53.895 --> 05:55.438
Nothing, other than
my stomach.

05:55.438 --> 05:58.483
Hmm. Do you think
it might be an infection?

05:58.483 --> 06:00.944
It's hard to say,

06:00.944 --> 06:04.239
but since there's no fever
or any other concerning signs,

06:04.239 --> 06:06.658
I think bed rest
is what's best for now.

06:06.658 --> 06:08.367
[SIGHS]
I'll be fine.

06:08.367 --> 06:10.037
Suit yourself,

06:10.037 --> 06:11.705
but if the pain
worsens,

06:11.705 --> 06:13.207
you let us know.

06:13.207 --> 06:14.624
Thank you.

06:14.624 --> 06:17.627
[♪♪♪]

06:17.627 --> 06:20.214
JULIE:
I'm so excited
for the wedding.

06:20.214 --> 06:21.422
ELIZABETH:
Me too.

06:21.422 --> 06:22.966
Whenever that is.

06:22.966 --> 06:24.592
I miss him so much.

06:24.592 --> 06:26.636
Well, of course,
you do!

06:26.636 --> 06:29.388
But now you have me
to keep you company.

06:29.388 --> 06:31.892
Hmm! Is that
why you're here?

06:31.892 --> 06:34.228
To keep me company?

06:34.228 --> 06:36.021
I can't fool you, can I?

06:36.021 --> 06:37.856
No, you can't.

06:37.856 --> 06:39.316
Okay. Well...

06:39.316 --> 06:41.818
I have been doing
a lot of thinking.

06:41.818 --> 06:44.363
Soul-searching, really...

06:44.363 --> 06:46.907
And I've landed on what
I want to do with my life.

06:46.907 --> 06:48.616
Oh?

06:48.616 --> 06:51.410
I want to be a teacher.

06:51.410 --> 06:52.787
Really?

06:52.787 --> 06:56.041
You? A-- A teacher?

06:56.041 --> 06:58.543
Why not?
I am good with kids,

06:58.543 --> 07:02.630
and I want to have an impact
on their lives, just like you.

07:02.630 --> 07:04.632
I know, but...

07:04.632 --> 07:06.260
I didn't make
a rash decision

07:06.260 --> 07:07.510
to become a teacher.

07:07.510 --> 07:09.137
I wanted to be one
my whole life.

07:09.137 --> 07:11.098
This isn't something
I just decided upon

07:11.098 --> 07:14.726
because other parts
of my life weren't working out.

07:14.726 --> 07:16.061
Is that what you think?

07:16.061 --> 07:18.897
That my life
isn't working out?

07:18.897 --> 07:20.941
Julie, I'm sorry.
That's not what I meant.

07:20.941 --> 07:23.193
Everyone just thinks
I'm this flighty girl

07:23.193 --> 07:25.028
who has no real direction.
Julie--

07:25.028 --> 07:27.197
But I am more than that,
Elizabeth,

07:27.197 --> 07:29.783
and I'm going
to prove it to you.

07:30.992 --> 07:33.954
And I appreciate
your conviction.

07:33.954 --> 07:36.831
But it takes hard work
to become a teacher.

07:36.831 --> 07:38.750
You have to observe
in the classroom,

07:38.750 --> 07:40.668
and study, and take
the boards--
I know

07:40.668 --> 07:44.089
I have a lot to learn,
which is why I came to you.

07:44.089 --> 07:46.049
I want to be
your apprentice!

07:46.049 --> 07:47.467
My apprentice?

07:47.467 --> 07:50.053
Exactly!
When can we start?

07:51.305 --> 07:52.472
Oh...

07:56.601 --> 07:58.228
Hey.
Hey.

07:59.896 --> 08:02.232
Ready to go?

08:02.232 --> 08:04.192
Have you been crying?

08:04.192 --> 08:06.111
No.

08:06.111 --> 08:07.612
You have.

08:07.612 --> 08:08.863
Jesse, it's nothing.

08:08.863 --> 08:10.615
No. Something's wrong.

08:12.700 --> 08:13.910
[INHALES DEEPLY]

08:13.910 --> 08:16.288
Today's my anniversary.

08:16.288 --> 08:18.123
[CHUCKLES, SNIFFS]

08:18.123 --> 08:20.208
The day I married Peter.

08:20.208 --> 08:22.210
It's sort of on my mind,
that's all.

08:24.879 --> 08:28.633
You want to just
skip tonight?

08:29.801 --> 08:32.679
You're a great guy, Jesse.

08:32.679 --> 08:34.431
You don't deserve this.

08:35.682 --> 08:37.725
I don't deserve you.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.103
[SNIFFLES]

08:40.103 --> 08:42.356
Hey...

08:42.356 --> 08:44.441
Why are you
looking at me like that?

08:44.441 --> 08:45.900
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

08:45.900 --> 08:49.404
I thought that I was ready
to move on.

08:50.489 --> 08:52.740
I don't know.
Maybe I'm not.

08:53.950 --> 08:55.369
What are you saying?

08:56.328 --> 08:58.746
[EXHALING]
Uh...

08:58.746 --> 09:00.832
Maybe we should
take a little break.

09:01.749 --> 09:03.251
Don't jump to that.

09:03.251 --> 09:04.919
It's your anniversary.
I get it.

09:04.919 --> 09:06.296
We'll be fine.

09:06.296 --> 09:08.382
We will...

09:08.382 --> 09:10.425
after a little break.

09:11.385 --> 09:13.594
We talking a "break"

09:13.594 --> 09:15.347
or "break-up"?

09:23.980 --> 09:26.525
Just a break.

09:27.817 --> 09:30.237
I need to collect
my thoughts.

09:30.237 --> 09:33.698
Get beyond this,
once and for all.

09:36.617 --> 09:37.702
Okay.

09:39.246 --> 09:41.456
[♪♪♪]

09:49.297 --> 09:52.259
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

09:55.303 --> 09:56.888
I suppose.

09:56.888 --> 09:58.515
CARSON:
You are the second person

09:58.515 --> 10:00.141
in a couple days
to come in.

10:00.141 --> 10:02.519
What do I have?
Maybe just a virus.

10:02.519 --> 10:03.770
Go home
and get some rest.

10:03.770 --> 10:05.355
I'll check on you
in a day.

10:05.355 --> 10:07.732
Thank you, Dr. Shepherd.
Yeah.

10:10.110 --> 10:11.945
So both of you
have a stomachache?

10:11.945 --> 10:13.405
Yes.

10:13.405 --> 10:16.366
There is something
going on here.

10:16.366 --> 10:19.369
Who's eaten out
in the last couple days?

10:19.369 --> 10:20.828
I-I have.
No.

10:20.828 --> 10:22.581
Have either of you
come into contact

10:22.581 --> 10:24.332
with someone
who had a stomachache?

10:24.332 --> 10:26.126
Not that I know of.
I don't think so.

10:26.126 --> 10:28.503
It's probably not
from a common eating place,

10:28.503 --> 10:30.671
and there's no clear
indication of a virus.

10:30.671 --> 10:32.757
I did feel myself
coming down with a cold,

10:32.757 --> 10:34.675
but my medicine
took care of that.

10:34.675 --> 10:36.595
Now I've got
this bad cramping.

10:36.595 --> 10:39.722
I had a headache yesterday,
and I took medicine for that.

10:39.722 --> 10:41.099
What medicine
did you take?

10:41.099 --> 10:43.017
BOTH:
Dr. Bellemore's
Miracle Tonic.

10:44.519 --> 10:45.686
Miracle Tonic?

10:51.276 --> 10:53.487
[♪♪♪]

10:54.571 --> 10:57.449
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

11:02.370 --> 11:05.248
I'm looking for
Mr. Archie Reed?

11:06.333 --> 11:08.418
Thank you.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.545
[CLEARS THROAT]

11:10.545 --> 11:11.796
Mr. Reed?

11:11.796 --> 11:13.298
Yeah?

11:13.298 --> 11:14.966
I'm Abigail Stanton.

11:14.966 --> 11:17.636
Oh! My character witness.

11:17.636 --> 11:19.179
Thank you for coming.

11:20.347 --> 11:21.806
Call me Archie.

11:21.806 --> 11:24.184
Your office told me
I could find you here, Archie.

11:24.184 --> 11:27.061
Well, they know me
very well.

11:27.061 --> 11:29.606
Have a seat.
Thank you.

11:31.525 --> 11:33.443
So how is
the trial going?

11:34.819 --> 11:37.197
Well, um...

11:37.197 --> 11:39.449
Oh. That good, huh?

11:39.449 --> 11:42.285
I got the attempted murder
and bribery charges dropped.

11:42.285 --> 11:45.372
That was the railroad
guy's doing, Ray Wyatt.

11:45.372 --> 11:47.582
But the misappropriation-
of-funds charge,

11:47.582 --> 11:50.168
that's hanging over Henry's head
like a guillotine.

11:50.168 --> 11:51.919
Yeah, I think he did that.

11:51.919 --> 11:54.548
I need to at least
humanize him.

11:54.548 --> 11:56.299
That's where you come in.

11:56.299 --> 11:59.052
Right after the prosecution
calls its last witness.

11:59.052 --> 12:00.387
You mean Bill Avery.

12:01.513 --> 12:02.972
Yeah, him.

12:04.098 --> 12:05.642
Hm.

12:06.560 --> 12:08.769
[♪♪♪]

12:11.730 --> 12:14.484
Oh, ho! Absolutely,
it cures gout.

12:14.484 --> 12:16.069
Just remember
the proper doses.

12:16.069 --> 12:18.154
And I'll see you Monday.

12:22.701 --> 12:24.160
Good day, sir!

12:24.160 --> 12:26.538
Ah-hah. Good day.

12:26.538 --> 12:28.956
I heard you been in town,
what, a couple days?

12:28.956 --> 12:30.250
That's right.

12:30.250 --> 12:31.668
Whatcha selling?

12:31.668 --> 12:34.087
Uh, health, vitality,
and a good disposition.

12:34.087 --> 12:36.381
What are you seeking?
"Dr. Lou Bellemore."

12:36.381 --> 12:38.883
What, are you a medical doctor?
No. No, I am not.

12:38.883 --> 12:41.135
I'm a practitioner
of the ancient healing arts

12:41.135 --> 12:44.138
that existed long before
there were medical schools.

12:45.098 --> 12:46.933
That is my best seller.

12:46.933 --> 12:49.561
It cures headaches,
colds, acne, even gout.

12:49.561 --> 12:51.812
And it'll put a little
spring in your step.

12:51.812 --> 12:52.813
What's in it?

12:52.813 --> 12:54.315
It's my own secret formula.

12:54.315 --> 12:56.192
Chock-full of vitamins
and minerals.

12:56.192 --> 12:57.902
Could you be
a little more specific?

12:57.902 --> 13:00.988
Sir...my formula
is my livelihood.

13:00.988 --> 13:02.156
And my secret.

13:02.156 --> 13:03.908
Hence the term
"secret formula."

13:04.992 --> 13:06.077
How much?

13:06.077 --> 13:07.995
Fifty cents.
Pretty steep.

13:07.995 --> 13:09.956
Can you put a price
on good health?

13:11.625 --> 13:12.833
[COINS JANGLING]

13:12.833 --> 13:14.502
Okay.

13:14.502 --> 13:16.212
Thank you.

13:24.345 --> 13:27.014
[♪♪♪]

13:27.014 --> 13:30.017
Perfect timing!
Hi, there.

13:30.017 --> 13:31.936
[QUIETLY]
So...

13:31.936 --> 13:33.020
Julie told me

13:33.020 --> 13:34.272
she wants to be
a teacher,

13:34.272 --> 13:36.065
and she wants to be
my apprentice!

13:36.065 --> 13:37.108
Oh. Dear.

13:37.108 --> 13:39.902
That is...daunting.

13:39.902 --> 13:41.988
I know my sister.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.364
Julie is
a wonderful person,

13:43.364 --> 13:44.823
but she likes
to have fun

13:44.823 --> 13:47.160
more than she likes to work.
I just don't think

13:47.160 --> 13:49.663
she has the commitment
it takes to be a teacher.

13:49.663 --> 13:51.122
Yes, I know.

13:51.122 --> 13:54.709
It takes a strong will
and a lot of patience

13:54.709 --> 13:57.170
to put up with those children
all day long.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.838
Rosemary, that's not what
being a teacher is all about.

13:59.838 --> 14:02.133
It's a destiny.
A calling.

14:02.133 --> 14:03.842
I just don't know
if it's Julie's.

14:03.842 --> 14:05.178
Have you discussed that
with her?

14:05.178 --> 14:06.805
No. I don't know
how to tell her.

14:06.805 --> 14:09.015
You shouldn't.
Excuse me?

14:09.015 --> 14:11.100
You should
show her.

14:11.100 --> 14:13.311
Just let Julie observe
you in the classroom

14:13.311 --> 14:15.896
for a few days. Once she sees
what it's really like,

14:15.896 --> 14:17.898
then she'll realize
it's not for her...

14:17.898 --> 14:20.234
or anyone else
with a refined constitution,

14:20.234 --> 14:21.820
for that matter.

14:21.820 --> 14:23.904
You know,
it's actually not a bad idea.

14:23.904 --> 14:26.491
Of course, it's not.
I don't have those.

14:26.491 --> 14:28.743
[CHUCKLES]

14:30.119 --> 14:31.663
[MUTTERS]
"I don't have those."

14:31.663 --> 14:34.833
[♪♪♪]

14:34.833 --> 14:37.043
Bill Avery.

14:37.043 --> 14:38.336
Miss Pardell!

14:38.336 --> 14:39.879
[CHUCKLES]
Please.

14:39.879 --> 14:41.589
Seeing how this
is our second round

14:41.589 --> 14:42.965
as witness
and prosecutor,

14:42.965 --> 14:44.551
call me Georgia.

14:44.551 --> 14:46.093
Have a seat.

14:46.093 --> 14:47.428
How many years
has it been?

14:47.428 --> 14:49.472
About nine?
Yeah.

14:49.472 --> 14:50.890
Now, as I recall,

14:50.890 --> 14:52.183
testifying isn't

14:52.183 --> 14:54.018
your favorite activity
in the world.

14:54.018 --> 14:56.813
[LAUGHS]
Next to being pinned
to a tree by a wild boar.

14:56.813 --> 14:58.898
I'll try not to take
that too personally.

14:58.898 --> 15:01.317
Please, don't. It's not you.
It's the other side.

15:01.317 --> 15:02.485
Then we're in agreement.

15:02.485 --> 15:04.153
I see them
as snakes in the grass.

15:04.153 --> 15:05.780
That works for me too.

15:05.780 --> 15:07.699
So, why did you
take this case?

15:07.699 --> 15:09.409
Henry Gowen.

15:09.409 --> 15:11.285
My entire office
was disappointed

15:11.285 --> 15:13.329
when he walked
in that mining case.

15:13.329 --> 15:14.706
But I'm taking
him down now.

15:14.706 --> 15:16.791
Well, sounds personal.

15:16.791 --> 15:19.043
It's personal to me when
someone escapes justice.

15:19.043 --> 15:20.587
Well, word
of caution.

15:20.587 --> 15:22.963
That guy's been known to be
a little slippery.

15:22.963 --> 15:24.173
Doesn't matter.

15:24.173 --> 15:25.966
You sound confident.

15:25.966 --> 15:28.052
I'm supremely confident.

15:32.807 --> 15:34.434
What do you smell?

15:34.434 --> 15:37.896
Menthol...
eucalyptus...

15:37.896 --> 15:39.731
maybe some honey?

15:43.818 --> 15:45.862
Now what do you smell?

15:47.906 --> 15:49.490
Garlic.

15:49.490 --> 15:51.910
You know what else
smells like garlic when heated?

15:51.910 --> 15:53.453
No.
Arsenic.

15:53.453 --> 15:56.080
[♪♪♪]

15:58.917 --> 16:00.668
So, what's the big deal?

16:00.668 --> 16:02.044
Arsenic is dangerous.

16:02.044 --> 16:03.546
Yeah, but it's
also medicine.

16:03.546 --> 16:05.632
We had the stuff
at my house growing up.

16:05.632 --> 16:07.634
Not anymore.
Too much of it can be fatal.

16:07.634 --> 16:09.719
How much is too much?
Depends, that's why

16:09.719 --> 16:11.638
it should be a doctor
administering it.

16:11.638 --> 16:14.056
Is that the law?
No! But it should be.

16:14.056 --> 16:16.768
Well, I'm not here to enforce
what should be the law.

16:16.768 --> 16:19.103
I'm not here to enforce
what is the law, either,

16:19.103 --> 16:21.522
but that's entirely--
People are getting sick.

16:21.522 --> 16:24.024
Four people
have gotten sick.

16:24.024 --> 16:25.985
And you don't know
if they're related.

16:25.985 --> 16:27.987
Rosemary made me chili
last week.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.363
I was sick for four days.

16:29.363 --> 16:31.365
You cannot tell her
I said that.

16:32.366 --> 16:33.743
What are you gonna do?

16:33.743 --> 16:35.662
I'm gonna continue to do
what I'm doing,

16:35.662 --> 16:38.372
and that is count every minute
till Bill gets back.

16:38.372 --> 16:40.583
I'm really sorry, Carson.
I can't help you.

16:40.583 --> 16:42.209
I wish I could.

16:42.209 --> 16:44.420
[♪♪♪]

16:47.966 --> 16:50.969
BILL:
I found AJ Foster
in Bishop Falls.

16:50.969 --> 16:52.762
GEORGIA:
And what did she tell you?

16:52.762 --> 16:54.180
BILL:
She told me

16:54.180 --> 16:56.265
when she was auditing
the bank's books,

16:56.265 --> 16:58.768
she found a paper trail
that showed that Henry Gowen

16:58.768 --> 17:02.229
was funneling town funds into
his own personal bank account.

17:02.229 --> 17:05.232
And that Ray Wyatt had
threatened her and bribed her

17:05.232 --> 17:07.151
to create
a new set of phony books.

17:07.151 --> 17:11.698
Are these the real set of books
that she provided you?

17:12.699 --> 17:13.992
Yes, that's them.

17:14.951 --> 17:16.953
No further questions.

17:23.167 --> 17:26.170
AJ Foster is currently
a fugitive, isn't that right?

17:26.170 --> 17:28.798
Yes, she is.
And she's wanted for,

17:28.798 --> 17:31.509
among other things,
lying under oath

17:31.509 --> 17:33.887
to the Inspector General,
correct?

17:34.846 --> 17:36.180
That's correct.

17:36.180 --> 17:39.099
So...she's a liar.

17:39.099 --> 17:40.768
She's not lying
about this.

17:40.768 --> 17:44.022
Well, liars lie. You don't know
the real truth.

17:44.022 --> 17:45.398
How could you?

17:45.398 --> 17:47.734
Ray Wyatt sent an assassin
to keep her quiet.

17:47.734 --> 17:49.360
That tells me
all I need to know.

17:49.360 --> 17:50.778
JUDGE:
I agree.

17:50.778 --> 17:53.031
Now change your line
of questioning, Mr. Reed,

17:53.031 --> 17:54.365
or sit down.

17:56.200 --> 17:59.328
[♪♪♪]

18:02.415 --> 18:05.125
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

18:17.179 --> 18:18.890
You looking for a table?

18:18.890 --> 18:21.350
[SCOFFS]
More like a seat
at a table.

18:21.350 --> 18:22.769
You're welcome to this one.

18:23.978 --> 18:25.730
Thank you.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.149
There you go.

18:30.735 --> 18:32.236
I'm Jesse Flynn.

18:32.236 --> 18:33.613
Pleasure to meet you.

18:33.613 --> 18:35.239
I'm Julie Thatcher.

18:35.239 --> 18:37.366
Oh! You must be
Elizabeth's sister.

18:37.366 --> 18:38.618
Yes, I am.

18:38.618 --> 18:40.036
Okay.

18:41.746 --> 18:43.289
What on Earth is that?

18:44.331 --> 18:47.167
Oh,
just some delicious beans.

18:47.167 --> 18:48.294
[BOTH LAUGHING]

18:48.294 --> 18:49.712
There's not much
on the menu.

18:49.712 --> 18:51.631
If you want more variety
and great food,

18:51.631 --> 18:53.841
you should check out
Abigail's cafe.

18:53.841 --> 18:55.676
So, why aren't you there?

18:56.970 --> 18:58.763
Um...

18:58.763 --> 19:00.139
my girl works there.

19:00.139 --> 19:01.933
At least...

19:01.933 --> 19:03.601
she was my girl.

19:03.601 --> 19:06.062
Last time we talked,
she asked for a break.

19:07.897 --> 19:11.067
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

19:13.360 --> 19:15.488
[♪♪♪]

19:15.488 --> 19:17.323
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

19:27.625 --> 19:29.251
ELIZABETH:
Good morning, everyone!

19:29.251 --> 19:31.545
Today, we have
a very special visitor.

19:31.545 --> 19:35.091
Please welcome my sister,
Miss Julie Thatcher,

19:35.091 --> 19:37.093
who is thinking
of becoming a teacher.

19:37.093 --> 19:39.846
STUDENTS:
Good morning,
Miss Thatcher!

19:39.846 --> 19:41.764
Thank you, Eliz--

19:41.764 --> 19:43.390
Miss Thatcher.
Mm-hm.

19:43.390 --> 19:45.434
Please, everyone,

19:45.434 --> 19:46.894
just do what you do.

19:46.894 --> 19:48.104
Don't mind me.

19:48.104 --> 19:50.023
Fly on the wall.

19:51.107 --> 19:53.776
[♪♪♪]

19:54.986 --> 19:56.487
All right, um, today,

19:56.487 --> 20:00.783
we will be starting
with a very exciting...

20:00.783 --> 20:04.078
geography quiz!

20:04.078 --> 20:06.455
[CLASS GROANS]

20:06.455 --> 20:08.332
All right,
who can think of a country

20:08.332 --> 20:10.877
that starts with
the letter G?

20:10.877 --> 20:12.461
LAURA:
Germany!

20:12.461 --> 20:13.963
ELIZABETH:
Very good.

20:13.963 --> 20:16.966
And on what continent
would we find Germany?

20:16.966 --> 20:18.467
CODY: Europe!
That's right!

20:18.467 --> 20:20.887
How about a country
that starts with the letter A?

20:20.887 --> 20:22.471
STUDENT:
Argentina.

20:22.471 --> 20:25.183
Mm-hmm. And if
we were visiting a continent,

20:25.183 --> 20:27.476
where would
we find Argentina?

20:28.227 --> 20:29.353
South America.

20:29.353 --> 20:31.064
ELIZABETH:
That's right! Very go--

20:31.064 --> 20:32.190
[SHRIEKS]

20:33.816 --> 20:35.234
[BOYS CHUCKLE]

20:36.443 --> 20:39.655
Um...C?

20:39.655 --> 20:40.781
China!

20:40.781 --> 20:41.741
Continent?

20:41.741 --> 20:43.617
Asia.

20:45.036 --> 20:47.413
[♪♪♪]

20:49.540 --> 20:51.250
D.

20:51.250 --> 20:53.002
Timmy?

20:54.628 --> 20:55.838
[STAMMERING]

20:55.838 --> 20:56.839
Um...

20:56.839 --> 20:57.965
Denmark.

20:58.883 --> 21:00.718
Continent, Robert?

21:00.718 --> 21:02.511
Europe?

21:02.511 --> 21:03.930
Correct.

21:03.930 --> 21:05.014
Timmy, Robert,

21:05.014 --> 21:06.599
if there's any more
misbehaving,

21:06.599 --> 21:08.976
you'll be staying inside
for recess.

21:08.976 --> 21:10.436
Okay, Miss Thatcher.

21:10.436 --> 21:12.063
Sorry, Miss Thatcher.

21:13.856 --> 21:16.442
Would you kindly liberate
this creature outdoors?

21:18.111 --> 21:20.404
Certainly. Ahem.

21:20.404 --> 21:22.448
Thank you.

21:22.448 --> 21:23.783
B?

21:23.783 --> 21:24.867
Burma.

21:24.867 --> 21:26.744
Good one, Timmy!

21:26.744 --> 21:28.121
H?

21:28.121 --> 21:30.623
[♪♪♪]

21:32.458 --> 21:34.668
You slept late!

21:34.668 --> 21:35.920
I know.

21:35.920 --> 21:37.296
I think all
the extra hours

21:37.296 --> 21:39.506
at the mill are
catching up with me.

21:39.506 --> 21:42.051
Oh, what's with
the big, fancy spread?

21:42.051 --> 21:44.386
Well, you have been
working so much at the mill

21:44.386 --> 21:46.305
and, of course,
being the sheriff,

21:46.305 --> 21:47.765
you have a lot
on your plate,

21:47.765 --> 21:50.143
so I decided you needed
a lot on this plate too.

21:50.143 --> 21:51.936
Sweetheart,
I'm not the sheriff.

21:51.936 --> 21:54.063
Lee Coulter,
you most certainly are.

21:54.063 --> 21:55.940
By the way,
where is your badge?

21:55.940 --> 21:57.524
The badge is in my pocket.

21:57.524 --> 22:00.402
You are the law
until Bill comes back.

22:00.402 --> 22:01.737
People need
to know that.

22:01.737 --> 22:03.281
Hmm.

22:03.281 --> 22:06.033
I just don't think I'm cut out
for it, that's all.

22:06.033 --> 22:08.494
I am sure,
in your short tenure,

22:08.494 --> 22:10.204
you will go down
in history

22:10.204 --> 22:11.664
as one of
the best sheriffs

22:11.664 --> 22:13.499
in the history
of all sheriffs.

22:13.499 --> 22:15.251
I appreciate your
confidence in me,

22:15.251 --> 22:17.044
it's very cute,
but I just don't--

22:17.044 --> 22:19.005
No. Just shh!

22:19.005 --> 22:21.174
You... are
a natural born leader.

22:21.174 --> 22:22.216
Mm.

22:22.216 --> 22:23.968
You are doing
a great job.

22:23.968 --> 22:25.928
Thanks, sweetheart.
Mm-hmm.

22:25.928 --> 22:28.055
One more.

22:29.974 --> 22:34.187
ELIZABETH:
Everyone, that concludes
our grammar lesson for the day.

22:34.187 --> 22:37.731
Now, for your homework, please
do pages 31 and 32 in your book.

22:37.731 --> 22:39.984
Is it time for art class yet,
Miss Thatcher?

22:39.984 --> 22:41.319
Why, yes, it is.

22:45.031 --> 22:46.364
Sorry!

22:46.364 --> 22:47.741
I heard
"Miss Thatcher"

22:47.741 --> 22:49.743
and I just figured
she was talking to me.

22:49.743 --> 22:51.037
[LAUGHS]

22:51.037 --> 22:52.913
Well, Laura, it is
time for art class,

22:52.913 --> 22:57.168
and today, we will continue
painting with watercolors.

22:57.168 --> 23:00.963
Mm. Would you please pass
these out for me, Miss Thatcher?

23:00.963 --> 23:02.548
Oh, I thought
you'd never ask.

23:02.548 --> 23:04.800
Thank you.

23:16.729 --> 23:18.898
Wow! That's really good.

23:18.898 --> 23:20.191
Thanks.

23:20.191 --> 23:22.735
I like the soft edges
of your sun,

23:22.735 --> 23:25.571
and the way it melts into
the sharper edges of the water.

23:25.571 --> 23:27.614
STUDENT:
I tried hard
to make that work.

23:27.614 --> 23:29.075
You used
the perfect mixture

23:29.075 --> 23:31.077
of paint and water
to achieve that effect.

23:31.077 --> 23:34.247
Do you want to help me
blend the colors of the sky?

23:34.247 --> 23:35.748
Of course!

23:35.748 --> 23:37.875
First...

23:37.875 --> 23:40.836
we'll need to start
with a thinner layer of blue.

23:40.836 --> 23:43.047
[♪♪♪]

23:47.968 --> 23:50.679
Opal, are you all right?

23:50.679 --> 23:52.430
No.

23:55.809 --> 23:56.936
There you go.

23:56.936 --> 23:59.479
Thank you, Doctor.
You got it.

24:03.025 --> 24:04.442
Oh, hey, Opal.

24:04.442 --> 24:06.362
Is your tummy
hurting?

24:06.362 --> 24:08.572
She says
she's in a lot of pain.

24:08.572 --> 24:11.575
Come.
Let's take a look at you.

24:14.954 --> 24:17.415
Did your mommy give you
medicine recently?

24:18.332 --> 24:19.666
Yeah?

24:19.666 --> 24:23.045
Was it in a blue bottle
called "tonic"?

24:23.045 --> 24:24.130
Yeah.

24:24.130 --> 24:26.464
[♪♪♪]

24:26.464 --> 24:27.465
Okay.

24:27.465 --> 24:30.219
You're gonna be
just fine.

24:31.804 --> 24:33.389
Come on.

24:33.389 --> 24:36.683
And then he said to me--
Wait, hold on a second.

24:36.683 --> 24:39.519
Hey, Julie!
Wait up.

24:39.519 --> 24:40.771
Hi, Jesse.

24:40.771 --> 24:42.440
I heard you were
in class today.

24:42.440 --> 24:43.565
That's right.

24:43.565 --> 24:45.025
We never stop
learning, do we?

24:45.025 --> 24:47.069
[JULIE LAUGHS]

24:54.952 --> 24:57.163
[♪♪♪]

25:16.598 --> 25:18.600
How are you doing, Henry?

25:20.602 --> 25:23.814
Well, I've had better days.

25:23.814 --> 25:26.984
And I imagine
I'm gonna have worse.

25:26.984 --> 25:29.236
I heard they dropped

25:29.236 --> 25:31.864
the attempted murder and bribery
charges against you.

25:31.864 --> 25:35.326
Well, I'm still
looking at 10 years

25:35.326 --> 25:37.036
for stealing town funds.

25:38.829 --> 25:40.456
Why did you do it, Henry?

25:42.749 --> 25:44.960
Why does anybody
do anything?

25:44.960 --> 25:47.880
I think
you owe me an explanation.

25:53.344 --> 25:57.390
Growing up,
I didn't have much of anything.

25:57.390 --> 26:00.267
Just a dirt floor
in a sharecropper's shack.

26:01.810 --> 26:03.561
If I wanted
something...

26:04.813 --> 26:06.232
I had to take it.

26:07.483 --> 26:09.860
And you never
stopped taking.

26:11.153 --> 26:12.988
Something like that.

26:15.074 --> 26:17.575
Look, I'm not--
I'm not holding out for mercy.

26:17.575 --> 26:20.204
[SCOFFS]
Well, I'll be
doing that for you.

26:21.621 --> 26:23.832
For all the bad things
I've done,

26:23.832 --> 26:25.834
I must've done
something right.

26:25.834 --> 26:27.169
Why is that?

26:28.670 --> 26:31.298
Because, for some odd reason
that I don't understand,

26:31.298 --> 26:33.300
you still seem
to believe in me.

26:41.225 --> 26:43.727
[♪♪♪]

27:00.369 --> 27:01.870
Easy, boys.

27:01.870 --> 27:03.080
Easy.

27:03.080 --> 27:05.332
We're going
for a little trip.

27:15.342 --> 27:17.595
Here we go.

27:25.436 --> 27:28.021
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

27:28.021 --> 27:30.399
Thank you.

27:30.399 --> 27:32.234
Thank you very much.
Now, tell me.

27:32.234 --> 27:35.279
What has surprised you
the most about being sheriff?

27:35.279 --> 27:37.156
Well, when I took the job,

27:37.156 --> 27:38.532
I didn't know
if I was gonna like it.

27:38.532 --> 27:40.658
[CHUCKLES]
Yes, I remember.
Mm-hm.

27:40.658 --> 27:43.203
I guess I would say
what surprised me most

27:43.203 --> 27:45.747
is just how much
I don't like it.

27:45.747 --> 27:47.166
[ROSEMARY LAUGHING LOUDLY]

27:48.584 --> 27:50.794
[♪♪♪]

27:57.384 --> 28:00.471
Well, Mr. Grumpy-Pants,
you are doing a great job.

28:00.471 --> 28:02.264
Peace reigns
over Hope Valley.

28:02.264 --> 28:04.642
Someone stole my wagon!

28:05.434 --> 28:06.519
Lee!

28:06.519 --> 28:08.312
Go!
Yes. Yes, yes, yes.

28:08.312 --> 28:09.522
We'll go. Okay.

28:12.525 --> 28:14.401
It was right there
and now it's gone.

28:14.401 --> 28:15.944
Are you sure
you tied it down?

28:15.944 --> 28:17.237
'Course I did.

28:17.237 --> 28:19.990
I don't want
you chasing horse thieves

28:19.990 --> 28:21.825
all through the night!
It's all right.

28:21.825 --> 28:24.328
I think I know who took it.
I'll be right back.

28:24.328 --> 28:25.787
Who?

28:30.668 --> 28:32.961
CARSON:
Good evening, Lee.

28:32.961 --> 28:34.712
Carson.

28:36.423 --> 28:38.634
Um...

28:38.634 --> 28:41.220
Unfortunately, I am here

28:41.220 --> 28:43.514
in my official capacity
as acting sheriff.

28:43.514 --> 28:45.474
Yeah, I figured.

28:45.474 --> 28:48.310
Mm-hmm.

28:48.310 --> 28:50.103
I don't really
have the skill set

28:50.103 --> 28:52.898
to get a confession
out of you, but...

28:52.898 --> 28:54.774
I don't think I need that,
do I?

28:54.774 --> 28:57.528
Nope. I took his wagon,
I hid it in the woods.

28:57.528 --> 29:00.030
Right. Well, um...

29:00.030 --> 29:02.115
I'm gonna need you
to give that back.

29:02.115 --> 29:03.825
That's not gonna happen.

29:04.951 --> 29:07.913
I was afraid
you were gonna say that.

29:07.913 --> 29:10.999
Lou Bellemore hasn't
broken any laws,

29:10.999 --> 29:13.043
that I can tell.

29:14.336 --> 29:15.629
But you just did.

29:17.839 --> 29:20.300
I'm sorry,
Carson.

29:22.678 --> 29:25.055
I have
looked everywhere.

29:25.055 --> 29:26.890
I understand.

29:26.890 --> 29:28.267
Elizabeth!

29:29.476 --> 29:31.186
Did you hear?

29:31.186 --> 29:32.354
Hear what?

29:32.354 --> 29:35.815
Clara told Dottie,
who told Florence,

29:35.815 --> 29:37.943
who told Molly--
What?

29:37.943 --> 29:39.194
Apparently, Julie

29:39.194 --> 29:41.363
is trying to steal
Jesse away from Clara.

29:41.363 --> 29:42.948
You can't repeat
a word of that.

29:42.948 --> 29:44.408
That has to stay
between the two of us.

29:44.408 --> 29:46.326
Rosemary, Julie has
only been in town

29:46.326 --> 29:47.536
for a couple of days.

29:47.536 --> 29:49.329
Now she's in
the schoolroom with me,

29:49.329 --> 29:50.581
as you suggested.

29:50.581 --> 29:52.124
Elizabeth,
it is only natural

29:52.124 --> 29:54.042
for you to want
to defend your sister,

29:54.042 --> 29:56.420
but truth is truth.

29:56.420 --> 29:58.464
And idle gossip
is idle gossip.

29:58.464 --> 29:59.548
Besides, I heard

29:59.548 --> 30:01.091
that Clara
and Jesse broke up.

30:01.091 --> 30:02.676
Well, who's
gossiping now?

30:02.676 --> 30:03.761
They did not break up.

30:03.761 --> 30:05.304
They are taking
a little break.

30:05.304 --> 30:07.431
There's a difference
between the two.

30:07.431 --> 30:09.558
NED:
Elizabeth?

30:09.558 --> 30:11.310
Telegram for you.

30:11.310 --> 30:12.770
ELIZABETH:
Thank you, Ned.

30:12.770 --> 30:14.271
Certainly.

30:15.355 --> 30:16.856
Is it Jack?

30:16.856 --> 30:18.484
Oh, no.
Is it bad news?

30:18.484 --> 30:21.987
It's not bad news,
but it isn't good news either.

30:21.987 --> 30:24.531
Lee, what's going on?

30:24.531 --> 30:26.366
I had to arrest him.

30:26.366 --> 30:28.201
Oh, goodness, Lee! What?

30:28.201 --> 30:29.995
I have to uphold
the peace, right?

30:29.995 --> 30:31.664
Because of
Lou Bellemore?

30:31.664 --> 30:33.791
That's ridiculous!
Opal was sick earlier.

30:33.791 --> 30:35.417
Carson said
it was his tonic.

30:35.417 --> 30:37.085
It is.
Well, I don't
know that.

30:37.085 --> 30:39.588
What're we gonna do
if someone needs an operation?

30:39.588 --> 30:42.174
You know how long it took to get
a doctor to come to this town?

30:42.174 --> 30:44.510
I tell you what,
just get me back my wagon back

30:44.510 --> 30:46.720
and I'll be on my way.
What, so you can sell

30:46.720 --> 30:48.639
your tonic in the next town?
No.

30:48.639 --> 30:50.557
I know the way.

30:50.557 --> 30:51.642
All right, let's go.

30:51.642 --> 30:53.185
Where?
Jail. You're going too.

30:53.185 --> 30:54.812
For what?
For being a nuisance.

30:54.812 --> 30:56.062
Michael, I need you too.

30:56.062 --> 30:57.439
Hickam?

31:09.743 --> 31:11.411
Uh-uh-uh-uh! No.

31:11.411 --> 31:13.413
Same cell.

31:15.624 --> 31:19.378
Now, Michael,
I'm not sure how this works,

31:19.378 --> 31:20.796
but you are now deputized.

31:20.796 --> 31:23.089
You need to keep an eye
on these guys tonight.

31:23.089 --> 31:25.008
Make sure
they don't kill each other.

31:25.008 --> 31:27.052
Am I really
a deputy?

31:27.052 --> 31:29.304
About as much
as I'm a sheriff.

31:29.304 --> 31:31.682
Good luck!

31:31.682 --> 31:33.433
[DOOR CLOSES]

31:33.433 --> 31:35.644
[♪♪♪]

31:45.111 --> 31:46.822
Good morning, sweetheart.

31:46.822 --> 31:48.907
Oh...kay.

31:50.992 --> 31:53.119
Ahem.

31:53.787 --> 31:55.581
[SIGHS]

31:55.581 --> 31:57.708
[THUMPS]

31:59.334 --> 32:01.795
Rosie, what choice did I have?
Oh, I don't know!

32:01.795 --> 32:04.172
Maybe not arresting
the town's only doctor

32:04.172 --> 32:05.424
just for doing his job?

32:05.424 --> 32:07.133
It's not his job
to be a vigilante.

32:07.133 --> 32:09.720
[SCOFFS]
You're such a stickler
for the law!

32:09.720 --> 32:11.388
I have to be!
I'm the sheriff.

32:11.388 --> 32:13.640
No thanks to you,
I might add.

32:14.516 --> 32:15.809
Listen.

32:15.809 --> 32:17.477
I'm not gonna
keep Carson in jail.

32:17.477 --> 32:19.145
You're not?

32:19.145 --> 32:21.273
Of course not! No!

32:21.273 --> 32:23.316
I don't know anything
about "sheriffing,"

32:23.316 --> 32:26.278
but, in business, when you have
two sides that can't agree,

32:26.278 --> 32:27.821
sometimes,
the best thing to do

32:27.821 --> 32:29.740
is to lock 'em
in a room together.

32:32.158 --> 32:34.953
Except, in this case,
the room...

32:34.953 --> 32:36.538
is a jail cell.

32:36.538 --> 32:37.664
Exactly.

32:38.957 --> 32:40.125
Now can I have my kiss?

32:40.125 --> 32:41.919
[CHUCKLES]

32:41.919 --> 32:43.962
Mm.

32:43.962 --> 32:45.505
And some breakfast.

32:45.505 --> 32:47.549
Please. Please.
Thank you.

32:47.549 --> 32:49.134
[LAUGHS]

32:49.134 --> 32:51.762
[♪♪♪]

32:54.222 --> 32:56.099
Laura is quite
the artist.

32:56.099 --> 32:58.644
Mm. Well, it was
your first love as a child too.

32:58.644 --> 33:00.103
Still is.

33:00.103 --> 33:02.063
There's a lot
you don't know about me.

33:02.063 --> 33:03.315
More than you know.

33:03.315 --> 33:04.900
Like the fact

33:04.900 --> 33:07.360
that you came to Hope Valley
under false pretenses.

33:07.360 --> 33:09.028
What are you talking about?

33:11.824 --> 33:14.117
Mother sent me
this telegram.

33:17.746 --> 33:18.747
You didn't tell them

33:18.747 --> 33:20.165
you were coming
to visit me,

33:20.165 --> 33:22.459
or that you were pursuing
a career in teaching.

33:22.459 --> 33:24.419
Because
they would've stopped me.

33:24.419 --> 33:26.672
I'm tired of living
under Father's thumb.

33:26.672 --> 33:28.173
He thinks
I'm a failure.

33:28.173 --> 33:30.467
Julie, I want you
to find your path.

33:30.467 --> 33:32.218
I really do.

33:32.218 --> 33:34.638
Telling me you had
Mother and Father's blessing,

33:34.638 --> 33:35.806
when you didn't...

33:35.806 --> 33:38.684
Okay, I'm sorry
I didn't say anything.

33:38.684 --> 33:40.018
To make matters worse,

33:40.018 --> 33:42.145
now you're spending
time with Jesse Flynn.

33:42.145 --> 33:44.105
Why is that a bad thing?

33:44.105 --> 33:46.316
Because he and his girlfriend
are on a break,

33:46.316 --> 33:47.526
and it doesn't
look good.

33:47.526 --> 33:48.861
I was giving him advice

33:48.861 --> 33:50.278
on how to win Clara back!

33:50.278 --> 33:52.113
You were?

33:53.406 --> 33:56.075
When I saw how much
he loved Clara,

33:56.075 --> 33:57.410
it touched my heart.

33:57.410 --> 34:00.038
He really
misses her, so...

34:00.038 --> 34:02.708
I was helping him figure out
how to get her back.

34:03.792 --> 34:05.502
Julie, I'm sorry,
I didn't know.

34:05.502 --> 34:08.547
That's right,
because you don't believe in me.

34:08.547 --> 34:10.256
Miss Thatcher,

34:10.256 --> 34:12.009
will you help us
play jump rope again

34:12.009 --> 34:14.135
like you did yesterday?
Please?

34:14.135 --> 34:15.929
Of course, girls!

34:15.929 --> 34:17.639
Let's go.

34:17.639 --> 34:19.850
[♪♪♪]

34:36.449 --> 34:38.744
CARSON:
You know,
I've been thinking.

34:38.744 --> 34:40.954
Since your tonic
just started hurting people,

34:40.954 --> 34:42.706
you must've recently
added arsenic.

34:42.706 --> 34:45.208
I told you,
my formula is secret.

34:45.208 --> 34:47.544
You're just
a snake-oil salesman

34:47.544 --> 34:48.837
out to make a quick buck.

34:48.837 --> 34:50.171
That is not true.

34:50.171 --> 34:51.256
For your information,

34:51.256 --> 34:52.966
when it comes
to curing what ails,

34:52.966 --> 34:55.385
there is a place for both of us.
No, there isn't.

34:55.385 --> 34:56.970
Long before
there were doctors,

34:56.970 --> 34:59.056
people were treating themselves
with herbs

34:59.056 --> 35:01.516
and a secret ingredient
they didn't even realize--

35:01.516 --> 35:03.351
Another secret ingredient?

35:03.351 --> 35:05.144
But this one
I'll tell you.

35:05.144 --> 35:08.398
It's called
the power of believing.

35:08.398 --> 35:11.735
And that is a miracle drug
science hasn't topped.

35:14.863 --> 35:17.616
[♪♪♪]

35:17.616 --> 35:19.701
When I first started
my practice...

35:20.702 --> 35:22.370
a 13-year-old girl
came in

35:22.370 --> 35:24.664
who hated looking at herself
in the mirror.

35:24.664 --> 35:26.416
She had some skin blemishes.

35:26.416 --> 35:28.085
I told her,
"Give it some time.

35:28.085 --> 35:30.420
It'll clear up."

35:31.379 --> 35:33.799
I was young.

35:33.799 --> 35:36.384
I couldn't see how much
it mattered to her.

35:36.384 --> 35:37.970
Had I been able to,

35:37.970 --> 35:41.347
maybe I could've stopped her
from taking a tonic.

35:41.347 --> 35:45.769
She nearly died
and was never quite the same.

35:45.769 --> 35:48.647
I know you think
you're helping people

35:48.647 --> 35:50.107
by adding arsenic,

35:50.107 --> 35:53.568
but more and more doctors
are moving away from it.

35:53.568 --> 35:55.570
You're actually
hurting people.

36:01.076 --> 36:02.619
ABIGAIL:
You ready to go?

36:02.619 --> 36:05.122
BILL:
Yeah. I want to talk
to you for a second.

36:07.833 --> 36:09.709
I don't want you
getting your hopes up

36:09.709 --> 36:12.378
that your testimony
is going to make a difference.

36:12.378 --> 36:14.923
Why is that?

36:14.923 --> 36:17.717
This judge is known
as the "hanging judge."

36:17.717 --> 36:19.678
Lots of judges
have that reputation.

36:19.678 --> 36:22.055
Well, this one
lives up to it.

36:22.055 --> 36:24.099
Bill, what aren't
you telling me?

36:26.977 --> 36:28.812
I heard this judge
had a son

36:28.812 --> 36:31.439
who'd get in trouble.
Nothing big.

36:31.439 --> 36:34.317
At 16, he took the neighbor's
horse for a joy ride.

36:34.317 --> 36:37.403
The neighbors were upset, but
they didn't wanna press charges.

36:37.403 --> 36:39.072
It didn't matter.
He took his kid,

36:39.072 --> 36:40.866
locked him in a room,
and called the sheriff,

36:40.866 --> 36:42.534
to have him come
and arrest him.

36:42.534 --> 36:44.995
The kid escaped
and ran away.

36:44.995 --> 36:46.579
What happened to him?

36:46.579 --> 36:48.915
They haven't heard from him
or seen him since.

36:48.915 --> 36:50.000
Oh, and if the judge

36:50.000 --> 36:51.459
would do that
to his own son,

36:51.459 --> 36:53.586
he's not going
to show Henry any mercy.

36:53.586 --> 36:56.297
He imposes the maximum
sentence in every case.

36:56.297 --> 36:58.299
[SIGHS]

37:01.761 --> 37:03.972
[♪♪♪]

37:14.524 --> 37:15.942
CARSON:
Lee.

37:15.942 --> 37:17.652
I'm ready to take him
to his wagon.

37:17.652 --> 37:19.529
Yeah, and I'm not
pressing charges.

37:19.529 --> 37:20.864
What about
the arsenic?

37:20.864 --> 37:23.366
We have
an understanding.

37:23.366 --> 37:24.868
Glad to hear it.

37:24.868 --> 37:26.745
Michael,
what are you waiting for?

37:26.745 --> 37:29.164
Put the sandwich down
and let 'em out.

37:32.000 --> 37:35.128
Henry is not
a perfect human being,

37:35.128 --> 37:36.963
but who among us is?

37:38.090 --> 37:41.467
As the new mayor
of Hope Valley,

37:41.467 --> 37:43.095
what would you say

37:43.095 --> 37:46.431
about your predecessor's
job performance?

37:47.432 --> 37:48.934
I've learned firsthand

37:48.934 --> 37:51.436
that it's not easy being a mayor
of a frontier town.

37:51.436 --> 37:53.855
You have to oversee
both the town council

37:53.855 --> 37:55.065
and law enforcement.

37:55.065 --> 37:56.733
People look to you
for answers,

37:56.733 --> 37:59.069
and everyone
has different priorities.

37:59.069 --> 38:01.571
Henry projected leadership
and made tough calls,

38:01.571 --> 38:03.115
and, as a result,

38:03.115 --> 38:06.076
he brought jobs to Hope Valley
and our town prospered.

38:06.076 --> 38:08.078
No further questions.

38:10.956 --> 38:15.376
GEORGIA:
Mr. Gowen basically
bankrolled your cafe, didn't he?

38:15.376 --> 38:16.836
I guess
you could say that.

38:16.836 --> 38:18.671
Did he also buy
your testimony today?

38:18.671 --> 38:20.132
He most certainly did not.

38:21.674 --> 38:24.136
He retrieved
your adopted daughter

38:24.136 --> 38:27.055
when she was stuck
in a storm.

38:27.055 --> 38:29.348
That has nothing to do
with my testimony.

38:29.348 --> 38:31.184
You feel beholden to him,
don't you?

38:31.184 --> 38:32.936
That doesn't change--
This is your way

38:32.936 --> 38:35.272
of paying him back.
He's part of my community!

38:35.272 --> 38:36.648
We help each other.

38:38.399 --> 38:39.818
Your Honor,

38:39.818 --> 38:41.486
if you're going
to judge the man,

38:41.486 --> 38:43.238
judge the whole man.

38:43.238 --> 38:45.157
The man who was willing
to take a bullet

38:45.157 --> 38:47.033
for Bill when
Ray tried to kill him.

38:47.033 --> 38:48.701
Yes, the man
who risked his life

38:48.701 --> 38:50.620
to bring my daughter home.

38:50.620 --> 38:53.372
I know you will decide
his guilt or innocence...

38:53.372 --> 38:56.459
but I would ask you
to remember

38:56.459 --> 38:59.004
that it's not wrong to give
someone a second chance

38:59.004 --> 39:02.007
or to believe in the power
of redemption.

39:03.300 --> 39:06.011
What's the alternative,
Your Honor?

39:06.011 --> 39:10.098
We may lose the person we love
and never see them again.

39:12.433 --> 39:14.269
CARSON:
Okay. There it is.

39:14.269 --> 39:16.688
The complete list
of all the minerals and vitamins

39:16.688 --> 39:19.816
that are safe for consumption.
LOU: New and improved formula!

39:19.816 --> 39:20.984
Yes, that it is.

39:20.984 --> 39:22.777
Sure to make people
twice as strong

39:22.777 --> 39:24.821
and at least
10 times smarter.

39:24.821 --> 39:27.157
Well, you know, let's
not get too carried away.

39:27.157 --> 39:28.200
Ah.

39:28.200 --> 39:31.786
[TONIC SPLASHING]

39:31.786 --> 39:34.455
The defendant will rise.

39:35.999 --> 39:37.792
Ahem.

39:39.836 --> 39:42.005
[♪♪♪]

39:47.260 --> 39:49.804
I find you, Henry Gowen...

39:51.056 --> 39:52.265
...guilty

39:52.265 --> 39:54.893
of the misappropriation
of public funds.

39:57.812 --> 40:00.357
I'm sentencing you
to 10 years,

40:00.357 --> 40:02.817
which is the maximum
allowed by statute.

40:07.405 --> 40:09.574
However,
as is my prerogative,

40:09.574 --> 40:11.243
I'm crediting you
with time served

40:11.243 --> 40:15.038
and granting you
immediate parole.

40:15.038 --> 40:17.249
Should you violate
the terms of this parole,

40:17.249 --> 40:19.625
you will be brought back
to serve the remainder

40:19.625 --> 40:20.877
of your sentence.

40:22.379 --> 40:26.007
You have one last chance,
Mr. Gowen.

40:26.966 --> 40:28.718
Don't make a fool of me.

40:29.886 --> 40:31.804
I will not, Your Honor.

40:31.804 --> 40:33.056
JUDGE:
We're done here.

40:33.056 --> 40:34.140
[GAVEL BANGS]

40:37.685 --> 40:39.896
[♪♪♪]

40:46.485 --> 40:50.782
That man has more lives
than a litter of cats.

40:52.742 --> 40:54.702
Come on.

40:54.702 --> 40:56.913
[♪♪♪]

40:58.039 --> 41:00.166
[ALL CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

41:04.212 --> 41:06.464
All right, class,
settle in.

41:08.800 --> 41:10.343
Now, today,

41:10.343 --> 41:13.721
we are going to be doing things
a little differently.

41:14.722 --> 41:16.349
Like what,
Miss Thatcher?

41:16.349 --> 41:17.976
Well, Opal, for one,

41:17.976 --> 41:20.353
we're going to let
the other Miss Thatcher

41:20.353 --> 41:21.604
start class.

41:21.604 --> 41:23.689
Today,

41:23.689 --> 41:25.275
Miss Julie Thatcher

41:25.275 --> 41:28.569
will be reading us a chapter
from an exciting book

41:28.569 --> 41:30.696
called...

41:30.696 --> 41:32.324
The Enchanted Castle.

41:32.324 --> 41:34.075
That's one
of my favorite books!

41:34.075 --> 41:35.701
I know.

41:35.701 --> 41:38.496
And I think that,
as my new teacher's apprentice,

41:38.496 --> 41:41.916
it's only right for you to be
the one to read it to the class.

41:41.916 --> 41:44.210
[SIGHS]

41:44.210 --> 41:45.420
[LAUGHS]

41:47.922 --> 41:50.508
I believe in you,
Julie, I do,

41:50.508 --> 41:54.137
and I think that you deserve
to follow your dreams.

41:55.305 --> 41:58.391
Thank you.
You will not regret this.

41:58.391 --> 41:59.851
[CHUCKLES]

42:04.481 --> 42:07.275
[INHALES DEEPLY]
Ahem.

42:07.275 --> 42:08.860
"There were three of them--

42:08.860 --> 42:11.070
"Jerry, Jimmy,

42:11.070 --> 42:13.281
"and Kathleen.

42:13.281 --> 42:15.283
"Of course,

42:15.283 --> 42:17.076
"Jerry's name was Gerald,

42:17.076 --> 42:20.497
"and not Jeremiah,
whatever you may think.

42:20.497 --> 42:22.207
"Jimmy's name was James,

42:22.207 --> 42:25.710
"and Kathleen was never called
by her name at all,

42:25.710 --> 42:27.295
"but Cathy,

42:27.295 --> 42:28.421
"or Catty,

42:28.421 --> 42:29.797
or Puss Cat..."

42:30.673 --> 42:32.884
[♪♪♪]
